{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Fig. 21, the database contains images with resolutions ranging from 720 × 576 pixels to 1920 × 1072 pixels, which have been organized into various folders according to their content.",
    "Park and Lee (2022) show 900 training images of Kvasir and 100 testing images in the dataset.",
    "As pixel-by-pixel segmentations, the ground truth annotations for each image are included in the dataset.",
    "To facilitate training and testing, each image was reduced to 384 × 384.",
    "proposed the Kvasir-SEG database derived from the prior Kvasir (Pogorelov et al. 2017) database."
  ]
}